headlines.description: — Zach LaVine and DeMar DeRozan each scored 23 points and the Chicago Bulls routed the injury-plagued Charlotte Hornets 121-91 on Friday night to take a big step toward reaching the NBA's play-in tournament.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine, DeRozan each score 23 points; Bulls rout Hornets

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — T.J. McConnell had 21 points, nine rebounds and eight assists, Jalen Smith added 12 points and 15 rebounds and the short-handed Indiana Pacers held off the playoff-hopeful Oklahoma City Thunder 121-117 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McConnell, Smith power Pacers past Thunder, 121-117

headlines.description: — James Harden sat at his locker inside the 76ers' new locker room — complete with oversized team logo in the center — and got his left ankle taped.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden, Embiid lead 76ers to 117-110 win over Raptors

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero is finishing strong in his bid for Rookie of the Year honors.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic rally in final quarter to beat Wizards 116-109

headlines.description: — The collective sentiment among the Celtics following their 41-point win at Eastern Conference-leading Milwaukee was it would be meaningless if they lost Friday's follow-up at home against Utah.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum's 39 lifts Celtics over short-handed Jazz 122-114

headlines.description: — Mikal Bridges remembers when he couldn't even score 30 points in a game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges has 42, Nets rout Hawks to boost lead for No. 6 seed

events.name: New York Knicks at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — With All-Star Julius Randle back in New York, the Knicks needed someone to step up.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson scores 48, Knicks down Cavs 130-116 without Randle

headlines.description: — Kevin Porter Jr. scored 33 points and Jalen Green added 32 to help the Houston Rockets end their seven-game losing streak with a 121-115 win over the Detroit Pistons on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets snap 7-game skid by beating Pistons 121-115

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane scored 22 points and Luke Kennard had 17 as the Memphis Grizzlies overcame a 20-point first-half deficit and beat the Los Angeles Clippers 108-94 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bane, Kennard help Grizzlies rally to beat Clippers 108-94

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis scored 17 of his 38 points in the fourth quarter and had 17 rebounds to lift the Los Angeles Lakers past Minnesota 123-111 and leapfrog the Timberwolves on Friday night in the crowded Western Conference <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Lakers overtake Timberwolves in standings with 123-111 win

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole cherishes all of the moments around superstars Stephen Curry and Klay Thompson, from the practice floor behind the scenes to under the bright lights and noise of game night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry, Poole, Thompson shoot Warriors past Spurs 130-115

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — De'Aaron Fox had 20 points and 11 assists and the playoff-bound Sacramento Kings won their second consecutive game against Portland Trail Blazers 138-114 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox has 20 points, playoff-bound Kings beat Blazers 138-114

headlines.description: — The Phoenix Suns are starting to string together some wins now that Kevin Durant is healthy.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant has 30 points, Suns beat Nuggets for 4th straight win
